::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' Please save this childish rhetoric for your thesis. You should be clear on the valuable import of this music party &mdash; it isn't some hallowed artistic hall, but a bargaining chip in the Penaconian market.
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' Only a prosperous, stable and vibrant Dreamscape can attract investors from all over the cosmos. An event ostensibly organized by students is indubitably the greatest exhibition showcase. We cannot miss this opportunity.
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' Which is why, I strongly recommend the Fortune Academy's student undertake the task of being the band leader, to control the overall impact of the party.
::'''Dreamweaver Academy Rep:''' Please be reminded: This is an academy. A venue that nurtures the elite should undoubtedly be led by the brightest minds.
::'''Dreamweaver Academy Rep:''' Grades are the most effective method in gauging a student's ability. The student with the best grade will become this band leader. Such a selection process will not invite any unwanted criticism.
::'''Charmony Academy Rep:''' Hmph. You dare debate me on music theory, you heap of scrap! This is a bad joke!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...What's going on?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Fight! Fight!
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' Whoa there, if it isn't the superstar that the kids like? Miss Robin, was it? During the assembly, you were vehemently outspoken on your insistence to organize the music party. Do you have any good ideas?
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' The performing band is a key position. Which institute should undertake this crucial role?
::'''Robin:''' ...
::'''Robin:''' I believe the reasons put forth by every rep are all for the sake of Paperfold University's overall benefit. I hope this music party will run like a perfectly well-oiled machine. In that case, I have a new proposal...
::'''Robin:''' Everyone take a step back, and leave the final decision to this Nameless beside me. How about it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Huh?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How about... deciding with a die roll?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What are the merits of music? I'll give it to whoever gets it right!
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' {{MC|f=Her|m=Him}}? I've never seen this person in the school before. Why should we bequeath such an authority to {{MC|f=her|m=him}}?
::'''Charmony Academy Rep:''' Hold on. I think this person is a stakeholder of Penacony.
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' S&mdash;Stakeholder? Ahem, about this matter... It's not that I'm doubting this stakeholder... but the music party is a longstanding interschool tradition with many complex layers of nuances woven between. There is simply too much context to understand...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Come on, cut me some slack.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are you worried that I can't handle it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Allow me to make it less complicated.
::'''Fortune Academy Rep:''' No, please do understand. This is an internal student matter, and it should be handled by...
::{{tx}}
